### ===========================================
### SecureCalculatorService — HTTP Tests
###
### SOAP Requests with apiKey and correlationId
### in the SOAP Header.
###
### Prerequisite: WildFly running with
### soap-header-security deployed.
### ===========================================

@host = http://localhost:8080
@app = soap-header-security
@ns = http://soap.training.cgsit.com/

### WSDL abrufen — beachte die <soap:header> Definitionen
GET {{host}}/{{app}}/SecureCalculatorService?wsdl
Accept: text/xml

### Addition: 10 + 20 (with valid API key)
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/SecureCalculatorService
Content-Type: text/xml

<soap:Envelope xmlns:soap="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/"
               xmlns:calc="{{ns}}">
    <soap:Header>
        <calc:apiKey>training-key-2025</calc:apiKey>
        <calc:correlationId>test-add-001</calc:correlationId>
    </soap:Header>
    <soap:Body>
        <calc:add>
            <a>10</a>
            <b>20</b>
        </calc:add>
    </soap:Body>
</soap:Envelope>

### Multiplikation: 6 * 7 (with valid API key)
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/SecureCalculatorService
Content-Type: text/xml

<soap:Envelope xmlns:soap="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/"
               xmlns:calc="{{ns}}">
    <soap:Header>
        <calc:apiKey>training-key-2025</calc:apiKey>
        <calc:correlationId>test-mul-002</calc:correlationId>
    </soap:Header>
    <soap:Body>
        <calc:multiply>
            <a>6</a>
            <b>7</b>
        </calc:multiply>
    </soap:Body>
</soap:Envelope>

### Division: 100 / 3 (with admin key)
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/SecureCalculatorService
Content-Type: text/xml

<soap:Envelope xmlns:soap="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/"
               xmlns:calc="{{ns}}">
    <soap:Header>
        <calc:apiKey>admin-key-2025</calc:apiKey>
        <calc:correlationId>test-div-003</calc:correlationId>
    </soap:Header>
    <soap:Body>
        <calc:divide>
            <a>100</a>
            <b>3</b>
        </calc:divide>
    </soap:Body>
</soap:Envelope>

### INVALID API key — should return SOAP Fault
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/SecureCalculatorService
Content-Type: text/xml

<soap:Envelope xmlns:soap="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/"
               xmlns:calc="{{ns}}">
    <soap:Header>
        <calc:apiKey>wrong-key</calc:apiKey>
        <calc:correlationId>test-fail-004</calc:correlationId>
    </soap:Header>
    <soap:Body>
        <calc:add>
            <a>1</a>
            <b>1</b>
        </calc:add>
    </soap:Body>
</soap:Envelope>

### MISSING API key — should return SOAP Fault
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/SecureCalculatorService
Content-Type: text/xml

<soap:Envelope xmlns:soap="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/"
               xmlns:calc="{{ns}}">
    <soap:Body>
        <calc:add>
            <a>1</a>
            <b>1</b>
        </calc:add>
    </soap:Body>
</soap:Envelope>

### Division with "user" role — should return SOAP Fault (requires "admin")
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/SecureCalculatorService
Content-Type: text/xml

<soap:Envelope xmlns:soap="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/"
               xmlns:calc="{{ns}}">
    <soap:Header>
        <calc:apiKey>training-key-2025</calc:apiKey>
        <calc:correlationId>test-role-005</calc:correlationId>
    </soap:Header>
    <soap:Body>
        <calc:divide>
            <a>100</a>
            <b>3</b>
        </calc:divide>
    </soap:Body>
</soap:Envelope>

### Division by zero — SOAP Fault (with admin auth, business error)
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/SecureCalculatorService
Content-Type: text/xml

<soap:Envelope xmlns:soap="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/"
               xmlns:calc="{{ns}}">
    <soap:Header>
        <calc:apiKey>admin-key-2025</calc:apiKey>
        <calc:correlationId>test-divzero-006</calc:correlationId>
    </soap:Header>
    <soap:Body>
        <calc:divide>
            <a>42</a>
            <b>0</b>
        </calc:divide>
    </soap:Body>
</soap:Envelope>
